      <section>
         <title>Setting options in MacOS X to be able to write in Sami</title>
         <p>To write in Sami you need a Sami keyboard.</p>
         <p>1. Open <strong>System Settings</strong></p>
         <p><img alt="Open &quot;System Settings&quot;" src="images/keyboard-open-systemprefs-osx10.5-swe.png" /></p>
         <p>2. Click <strong>International</strong> :</p>
         <p><img alt="System Settings" src="images/keyboard-selectintl-osx10.5-swe.png" /></p>
         <p>3. Click the <strong>Keyboard menu</strong> tab and toggle <strong>Northern Sami:</strong></p>
         <p><img alt="Adding a Sami keyboard" src="images/keyboard-select_se_keyboard-osx10.5-swe.png" /></p>
         <p>4. When you would like to write in Sami, choose the Sami keyboard in the Keyboard menu:</p>
         <p><img alt="Choose the Sami keyboard" src="images/keyboard-keyboard_menu-osx10.5-swe.png" /></p>
      </section>
